parameters:
\N<Luda Soldier>Lady, it's about time for your turn. Please move to the
waiting room.

\N<Luda Soldier>Before that, let me check the roster... What was your name
again...?
\N<Luda Soldier>Hmm... You're quite composed for a first battle.

\N<Rame>...Is that a problem? Would you prefer to see me panic and
flustered?

\N<Rame>Yes, I have fought here before. Although at that time, I
could do nothing but face defeat.

\N<Luda Soldier>I see, a veteran then. That's good, your opponent today
seems to be a man who also studied at the training grounds
of this town. His name was Fu-... something, wasn't it?
\N<Luda Soldier>Now, enough chit-chat. It's time to start preparing.
\N<Young Man>Ah, wait a moment. Please wait.
\N<Luda Soldier>Who are you...? How did you get in here?

\N<Young Man>Don't be suspicious. Geez, I went through the proper
procedures, okay? Might have been a bit rough though...
\N<Luda Soldier>You mean you took out the guards... What do you want?

\N<Young Man>She's about to fight, right? Good, I made it in time. I want
you to let me fight in her place.

\N<Young Man>Yeah, that would be better for you too, right soldier? After
all, this tournament is to select the strongest, isn't it?
\N<Luda Soldier>Are you out of your mind?

\N<Young Man>Huh? Is that wrong? Did the purpose change while I wasn't
aware?

\N<Rame>Wait. I don't know who you are but if you'd just listen
quietly...

\N<Rame>Are you implying that I'm weak? You're not from this town,
are you? I have no reason to be told such things by someone
who doesn't even know me.

\N<Young Man>Eh? No way, I'm not ignorant. After all, you're going to
marry me soon.

\N<Young Man>Yes, marry. Right? Soldier, it's okay if it's family, right?
There should be no problem with me taking her place as a
proxy.
\N<Rame>Could it be... could you possibly be...
\N<Riia>I'm back, Rame-chan. I've come to fulfill our promise.
